p:
Initial seedling height, elevation, and soil moisture all positively influenced S. chrysophylla survival. The effect of origin was not informative in the highest-ranked model alone or as an interaction term (w
i = 0.32; Table in S4 Table). Taller initial seedling heights increased survival probability by 292%, while seedlings at higher elevations and those with high soil moisture increased survival probability by 174% and 169%, respectively.
